      <hedline>
        <hl1>Correction</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of Apr 1 article and picture caption about Getty Conservation Institute (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article and a picture caption last Sunday about the Getty Conservation Institute's effort to document all the ways photographs have been developed over the years misidentified an instrument used to analyze the chemical makeup of old prints. It is an X-ray fluorescence spectrometer, not an infrared spectrometer. (The infrared instrument is also used in such work.)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article and a picture caption last Sunday about the Getty Conservation Institute's effort to document all the ways photographs have been developed over the years misidentified an instrument used to analyze the chemical makeup of old prints. It is an X-ray fluorescence spectrometer, not an infrared spectrometer. (The infrared instrument is also used in such work.)</p>
      </block>
